element.description: Overrides the default element name ('THEAD') to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider.

stickyHeader.description: Makes the table head stick to the top of the window as the user scrolls a long table

top.description: Allows manual control of the top offset, used in conjunction with `stickyHeader`

element.description: Overrides the default element name ('TABLE') to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider.

isActionable.description: Sets the table to visually display the actionable state of an interactive table. Mainly used for Data Grid.

noWrap.description: Sets the table cells to not line wrap.

scrollHorizontally.description: Sets the table to scroll horizontally on small screens.

striped.description: Sets a background color for even rows within the table.

tableLayout.description: Sets the `table-layout` style of the Table.

variant.description: Sets the `border` style of the Table.

element.description: Overrides the default element name ('TD') to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider.

textAlign.description: Sets the text alignment of the content within the Table cell.

whiteSpace.description: Sets how white space inside the Table cell is handled.

element.description: Overrides the default element name ('TH') to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider.

textAlign.description: Sets the text alignment of the content within the Table cell.

whiteSpace.description: Sets how white space inside the Table cell is handled.

width.description: Sets the width of a Table cell.

element.description: Overrides the default element name ('TR') to apply unique styles with the Customization Provider.

verticalAlign.description: Sets the vertical alignment of the content within the Table row.
